.TH "i2c_hid_set_or_send_report" 9 "i2c_hid_set_or_send_report" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i2c_hid_set_or_send_report \- forward an incoming report to the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i2c_hid_set_or_send_report
.BI "(struct i2c_client *client "  ","
.BI "u8 reportType "  ","
.BI "u8 reportID "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t data_len "  ","
.BI "bool use_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "client" 12
the i2c_client of the device
.IP "reportType" 12
0x03 for HID_FEATURE_REPORT ; 0x02 for HID_OUTPUT_REPORT
.IP "reportID" 12
the report ID
.IP "buf" 12
the actual data to transfer, without the report ID
.IP "data_len" 12
size of buf
.IP "use_data" 12
true: use SET_REPORT HID command, false: send plain OUTPUT report
